Token.Abstract: A PWIndoorLocation object represents the location data generated by a PWLocationManager object. This object incorporates the geographical coordinates of the deviceâ€™s location along with the floor ID, if available. This object conforms to the PWLocation protocol.
Initializes and returns a location object with the specified latitude and longitude.

Parameter.Name: latitude
Parameter.Abstract: The latitude of the coordinate point.

Parameter.Name: longitude
Parameter.Abstract: The longitude of the coordinate point.

Parameter.Name: timestamp
Parameter.Abstract: The time at which the location was reported.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A location object initialized with the specified coordinate point and timestamp.

Token.Abstract: Initializes and returns a location object with the specified coordinate information.

Parameter.Name: coordinate
Parameter.Abstract: A coordinate structure containing the latitude and longitude values.

Parameter.Name: floorID
Parameter.Abstract: The floor ID associated with the location object. If the floor ID is unknown or unspecified, initialize with kPWUnknownFloorID.

Parameter.Name: timestamp
Parameter.Abstract: The time at which the location was reported.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A location object initialized with the specified information.

Token.Abstract: Initializes and returns a location object with the specified coordinate information.

Parameter.Name: coordinate
Parameter.Abstract: A coordinate structure containing the latitude and longitude values.

Parameter.Name: floorID
Parameter.Abstract: The floor ID associated with the location object. If the floor ID is unknown or unspecified, initialize with kPWUnknownFloorID.

Parameter.Name: hAccuracy
Parameter.Abstract: The accuracy of the coordinate value. Specifying a negative number indicates that the horizontal accuracy value is invalid.

Parameter.Name: timestamp
Parameter.Abstract: The time at which the location was reported.

ReturnValue.Abstract: A location object initialized with the specified information.
